# Optional: copy to `.env.local` or adjust `.env.development`.
#
# **Backend URL — `VITE_API_BASE_URL` (required for explicit hosts; see `src/lib/apiConfig.ts`)**
# - Empty: browser calls `/v1/...` on the dev server; Vite proxies `/v1` to the same host as below (default 127.0.0.1:8000).
# - Set full origin (no `/v1` suffix): browser calls the API directly; configure CORS on the backend.

VITE_USE_LIVE_API=true
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Use demo registration/login with no backend.
# VITE_USE_MOCK_API=true

# Backend must use the same public URL for verification links in emails:
# PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:5173  (in afri-trust-backend/.env)
